.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,523]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">
Diagnosis to distinguish 
<taxonomicName box="[466,674,326,349]" class="Insecta" family="Chorotypidae" genus="Hydrolutos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breweri">
<emphasis box="[466,674,326,349]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Hydrolutos breweri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species was published previously (
<bibRefCitation author="Derka" box="[1054,1302,326,349]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" refString="Derka, T. &amp; Fedor, P. (2010) Hydrolutos breweri sp. n., a new aquatic Lutosini species (Orthoptera: Anostostomatidae) from Churi-tepui (Chimanta Massif, Venezuela). Zootaxa, 2653, 51 - 59." type="journal article" year="2010">
Derka and Fedor 
<number box="[1245,1302,326,349]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), however it requires more detailed analyses on females described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Issa" box="[775,1007,361,384]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" refString="Issa, S. &amp; Jaffe, K. (1999) Hydrolutos: un genero nuevo y cuatro especies nuevas de Lutosini Neotropicales (Orthoptera: Anostostomatidae). Nouv. Revue Ent. (N. S.), 16, 2, 111 - 121." type="journal article" year="1999">
Issa and Jaffe (
<number box="[941,999,361,384]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Clypeus of 
<taxonomicName box="[1146,1263,361,384]" class="Insecta" family="Chorotypidae" genus="Hydrolutos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breweri">
<emphasis box="[1146,1263,361,384]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">H. breweri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is undisputedly subtriangular (in both sexes), as presented in the original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Derka" box="[921,1182,396,419]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" refString="Derka, T. &amp; Fedor, P. (2010) Hydrolutos breweri sp. n., a new aquatic Lutosini species (Orthoptera: Anostostomatidae) from Churi-tepui (Chimanta Massif, Venezuela). Zootaxa, 2653, 51 - 59." type="journal article" year="2010">
Derka and Fedor (
<number box="[1115,1174,396,419]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Therefore &quot;a triangular clypeus&quot; mentioned in the Diagnosis (
<bibRefCitation author="Derka" box="[556,798,430,453]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" refString="Derka, T. &amp; Fedor, P. (2010) Hydrolutos breweri sp. n., a new aquatic Lutosini species (Orthoptera: Anostostomatidae) from Churi-tepui (Chimanta Massif, Venezuela). Zootaxa, 2653, 51 - 59." type="journal article" year="2010">
Derka and Fedor 
<number box="[743,798,430,453]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) has to be corrected as lapsus calami to &quot;subtriangular&quot;.
</paragraph>
